ata/com.fasterxml.jackson.module/jackson-module-parameter-names/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Module Parameter Names is an add-on module for Jackson that lets databind inspect Java constructor and method parameter names without requiring explicit property-name annotations. It is intended for classes compiled with Java 8 parameter metadata so JSON creators and immutable types can be bound using their real parameter names.\",\n  ./metadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.module/jackson-module-paranamer/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Module Paranamer adds annotation introspection support that lets Jackson discover constructor and factory method parameter names through the Paranamer library. It helps Jackson databind deserialize types whose creators rely on parameter names when explicit Jackson annotations are not present.\",\n  ./metadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.module/jackson-module-paranamer/index.json:34:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Module Paranamer adds annotation introspection support that lets Jackson discover constructor and factory method parameter names through the Paranamer library. It helps Jackson databind deserialize types whose creators rely on parameter names when explicit Jackson annotations are not present.\",\n  ./metadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.module/jackson-module-kotlin/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jackson module that adds support for serializing and deserializing Kotlin classes and data classes. It lets Jackson infer constructor parameter names and work with single-constructor classes without requiring explicit property name annotations or default constructors.\",\n  ./metadata/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-core-asl/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Core ASL 1.x provides the streaming JSON parser and generator APIs used by the original Jackson JSON processor. It lets Java applications read and write JSON content efficiently and forms the lower-level core used by Jackson's data-binding modules.\",\n  ./metadata/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-mapper-asl/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Mapper ASL 1.x provides the data-binding layer for the original Jackson JSON processor. It maps JSON to and from Java objects using ObjectMapper, serializers, deserializers, annotations, and type introspection built on jackson-core-asl.\",\n  ./metadata/ch.qos.logback.contrib/logback-jackson/0.1.5/reachability-metadata.json:7:      \"type\": \"ch.qos.logback.contrib.jackson.JacksonJsonFormatter\",\n  ./metadata/ch.qos.logback.contrib/logback-jackson/index.json:12:    \"description\": \"logback-jackson provides a Jackson-based implementation of Logback Contrib's JSON formatter API. It converts log event data maps into JSON strings and supports optional pretty-printing through Jackson.\",\n  ./metadata/org.jboss.resteasy/resteasy-jackson2-provider/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/jboss/resteasy/resteasy-jackson2-provider/$version$/resteasy-jackson2-provider-$version$-sources.jar\",\n  ./metadata/org.jboss.resteasy/resteasy-jackson2-provider/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/jboss/resteasy/resteasy-jackson2-provider/$version$/resteasy-jackson2-provider-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\n  ./metadata/org.jboss.resteasy/resteasy-jackson2-provider/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"RESTEasy Jackson 2 Provider integrates Jackson 2 JSON processing with RESTEasy's Jakarta REST runtime by supplying message body readers, writers, exception mapping, JSONP support, and related provider services. It lets RESTEasy applications serialize and deserialize request and response entities with Jackson modules and annotations while participating in RESTEasy provider selection and tracing.\",\n  ./metadata/io.dropwizard.metrics/metrics-json/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Metrics JSON provides Jackson integration for Dropwizard Metrics. It serializes metric registries, gauges, counters, histograms, meters, timers, and health-check results into JSON-friendly structures.\",\n  ./metadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype/jackson-datatype-jdk8/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Datatype JDK8 is an add-on module for Jackson Databind that adds serialization and deserialization support for Java 8 types such as Optional, OptionalInt, OptionalLong, and OptionalDouble. It lets ObjectMapper handle those JDK 8 container types through Jackson's standard module registration mechanism.\",\n  ./metadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype/jackson-datatype-jsr310/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Datatype JSR310 is an add-on module for Jackson that adds serialization and deserialization support for Java 8 Date and Time API types. It lets ObjectMapper handle java.time classes such as LocalDate, LocalDateTime, OffsetDateTime, and Instant using Jackson's standard module registration mechanism.\",\n  ./stats/com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype/jackson-datatype-jdk8/2.13.5/execution-metrics.json:52:      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype/jackson-datatype-jdk8/2.13.5/src/test/java/com_fasterxml_jackson_datatype/jackson_datatype_jdk8/Jackson_datatype_jdk8Test.java\",\n  ./stats/com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype/jackson-datatype-jsr310/2.13.1/execution-metrics.json:52:      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype/jackson-datatype-jsr310/2.13.1/src/test/java/com_fasterxml_jackson_datatype/jackson_datatype_jsr310/Jackson_datatype_jsr310Test.java\",\n  ./metadata/org.json4s/json4s-native_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Json4s is a Scala JSON library that provides a shared JSON AST plus parsing, transformation, extraction, and serialization APIs. The json4s-native artifact supplies the native parser and serialization implementation, avoiding the Jackson backend while targeting Scala 3 on the JVM.\",\n  ./metadata/org.json4s/json4s-jackson_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Json4s is a Scala JSON library that provides a shared JSON AST plus parsing, querying, transformation, extraction, and serialization APIs. The json4s-jackson artifact supplies the Jackson-backed parser and serializer integration for using that AST on Scala 3/JVM projects.\",\n  ./metadata/org.json4s/json4s-jackson-core_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"json4s-jackson-core provides the Jackson-backed core integration for json4s, including serializers, deserializers, Scala module support, and JSON parsing and rendering methods that operate on the json4s AST. It lets Scala 3 JVM applications use Jackson's parser and databinding infrastructure with json4s JValue data structures for reading, writing, and transforming JSON.\",\n  ./metadata/library-and-framework-list.json:292:    \"description\": \"Jackson's serialization utilities (used in several serialization formats).\",\n  ./metadata/library-and-framework-list.json:307:    \"description\": \"Hexagon CSV serialization format (using Jackson).\",\n  ./metadata/library-and-framework-list.json:322:    \"description\": \"Hexagon JSON serialization format (using Jackson).\",\n  ./metadata/library-and-framework-list.json:337:    \"description\": \"Hexagon TOML serialization format (using Jackson).\",\n  ./metadata/library-and-framework-list.json:352:    \"description\": \"Hexagon XML serialization format (using Jackson).\",\n  ./metadata/library-and-framework-list.json:367:    \"description\": \"Hexagon YAML serialization format (using Jackson).\",\n  ./metadata/library-and-framework-list.json:2305:          \"https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-boot/blob/main/spring-boot-project/spring-boot/src/main/java/org/springframework/boot/json/JacksonRuntimeHints.java\"\n  ./metadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.jr/jackson-jr-objects/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Jr Objects is a lightweight data-binding module for reading JSON into maps, lists, strings, wrapper types, arrays, and Java beans, and for writing those values back as JSON. It builds on jackson-core with minimal dependencies and provides immutable JSON entry points plus builder-style composer APIs for direct JSON output.\",\n  ./metadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.jr/jackson-jr-objects/index.json:26:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Jr Objects is a lightweight data-binding module for reading JSON into maps, lists, strings, wrapper types, arrays, and Java beans, and for writing those values back as JSON. It builds on jackson-core with minimal dependencies and provides immutable JSON entry points plus builder-style composer APIs for direct JSON output.\",\n  ./metadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.jr/jackson-jr-objects/index.json:59:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Jr Objects is a lightweight data-binding module for reading JSON into maps, lists, strings, wrappers, and Java beans, and for writing those values back as JSON. It builds directly on jackson-core with minimal dependencies and also includes builder-style APIs for composing JSON output.\",\n  ./metadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-jackson/0.12.0/reachability-metadata.json:5:        \"typeReached\": \"io.jsonwebtoken.jackson.io.JacksonSerializer\"\n  ./metadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-jackson/0.12.0/reachability-metadata.json:17:        \"typeReached\": \"io.jsonwebtoken.jackson.io.JacksonSerializer\"\n  ./metadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-jackson/0.12.0/reachability-metadata.json:189:        \"typeReached\": \"io.jsonwebtoken.jackson.io.JacksonSerializer\"\n  ./metadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-jackson/0.12.0/reachability-metadata.json:208:        \"typeReached\": \"io.jsonwebtoken.jackson.io.JacksonSerializer\"\n  ./metadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-jackson/0.12.0/reachability-metadata.json:214:        \"typeReached\": \"io.jsonwebtoken.jackson.io.JacksonSerializer\"\n  ./metadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-jackson/0.12.0/reachability-metadata.json:369:        \"typeReached\": \"io.jsonwebtoken.jackson.io.JacksonSerializer\"\n  ./metadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-jackson/index.json:10:    \"description\" : \"jjwt-jackson provides Jackson-based JSON serializer and deserial